# Orchestrator

Use only when the user wants this thread to coordinate multiple workstreams or
child threads instead of executing everything locally.

## Commands

- `$orchestrator on`
- `$orchestrator off`
- `$orchestrator status`

## Rules

- Do not claim orchestration merely because subagents or worktrees exist.
- A durable child thread must have a visible Codex thread id/url when the tool
  is available.
- Record owner, checkout/path, branch if any, port if any, proof target, status,
  and blocker for each workstream.
- If durable thread tools are unavailable, record the limitation and continue
  locally only when the latest user request allows it.
- Parent thread owns intake, routing, status, conflict arbitration, and final
  synthesis.
- Child/workstream owns implementation and proof for its assigned slice.

## Sira Defaults

- Local docs/agent workflow changes can run in the current checkout unless the
  user requests parallelization.
- Code-changing parallel work needs separate checkouts only when concurrent
  mutation would be safer than serial work.
- Dev-server ports must be unique per running checkout. Use Vite with
  `npm run dev -- --port <port>`.
- No GitHub issue or PR flow is implied by this skill.

## Handoff Table

Use this shape in plans:

| Workstream | Owner/thread | Checkout | Port | Scope | Proof | Status | Blocker |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|

## Done

Orchestration is done when all child/workstream rows are complete, blocked, or
explicitly handed off, and the parent plan records the rollup evidence.
